After installing android studio                                                                  .................................
    
    Installation of "SDK"  :
    
    1.first go on  " Tools " tab in android studion
    2.After then Select SDK manager
    3.After then  a new page open i.e "Settings for New Projects"
    4.After then go on "sdk platform"
    5.select and tick on latest version of sdk ...in my case Android 9 (Q+)
    6. click apply and ok 
    
    INstallation of "NDK" :
    7.After completing above step go on "sdk tools " tab 
    8.select lldb ,ndk,cmake,anadroid emulator,android sdk platforms ,android sdk tools,Android support repo, Google repo.
    
    THIS IS THE LINK WE CAN ALSO INSTALLATION OF NDK
    https://developer.android.com/ndk/guides
    
At in last step we have to do setup for Run and Test Android Studio Apps On Hardware Device       .................................

